\DOC best

\TYPE {best : (('a * 'a -> bool) -> 'a list -> 'a)}

\SYNOPSIS
Choses the best elemet from a list using a given ordering relation.

\LIBRARY window

\DESCRIBE
{best f l} choses the best element in {l} according to the ordering
{f}.

\FAILURE
Never fails.

\EXAMPLE
{
- best (fn (a,b) => a >= b) [1,10,2,9,3,8,4,7,5,6];
val it = 10 : int
}

\SEEALSO
sort, merge.

\ENDDOC
